General FAQ

This document is a community driven full breakdown of the respective class. This is a live document where we actively change it based on feedback and changes to the game to provide the best information to the community. The majority of us hang around in the Community Lost Ark Discord in our respective class channels. If you would like to give us feedback or ask questions contact us there.

Why should I play this class?

Summoner is a ranged caster who has a wide variety of skills and tools that are beneficial in any scenario. She has strong consistent damage uptime for very little skill required to maintain, an excellent class to learn and prog new raids with. Because of her High Stagger/ Weakpoint damage she brings to the party. Summoner is the swiss army knife of mages, allowing her to be flexible in all encounters.

How does my identity work?

The Summoner’s identity consists of 5 Ancient Spirit Summons and utilizes orbs as a cost for each summon.

(The Master Summoner engraving adds secondary effects to each individual Ancient Spirit as well as adding additional visual effects.)

What are my Party Synergies?

Synergies are a buff your party benefits from. These only apply to your party and not the entire raid. Consistent synergies are up for most of the fight while Burst synergies are much more infrequent.

What are the key pieces of my build?

Crit

Summoner always needs to hit a minimum 60% crit rate to make Keen Blunt Weapon 16% damage increase. Since she does not have any built in crit damage, KBW is a core engraving for her as it has very good scaling potential the more crit you have. For swift  builds you only need to hit 1630 swiftness minimum for +28% movement speed allowing you to hit cap movement speed with level 3 yearning set buff from supports.

Runes

Spec Master Summoner really benefits from Wealth Runes and high Specialization to build meter and more spec means a bigger margin of error on meter and higher damage as well. Master Summoner is the highest spec scaling class in the game. Shurdi will always keep 100% bleed uptime for any summoner build. Communication Overflow will benefit greatly from Quick Recharge runes being able to proc off of both the summoning of a pet as well as usage of their active skill

Skill Points

& Tripods

High Amount of Skill Points, you have to spec pretty far into the most skills. Summoner also needs level 4-5 tripods. Especially on her key tripods like Quick Prep on , attack power increase tripods on  and most importantly the crit tripod on .

Why is Yearning important?

It’s considered a part of a build despite not being on your character.

Swamp of Yearning is used by supports and gives +8/10/12% Damage and Attack/Move speed to the party. This is a Relic Set they use that has a golden ring.

Master Summoner

Written by Shengshui and Mugician

Playstyle

Consistent Burst playstyle *Similar to Deathblow Striker, and Surge Deathblade*. Slow, but has big numbers. Has more flexibility in raids due to more Identity Gauge generation. However, it has very long cooldowns and is reliant on high level CD gems. Due to the lack of mobility, the long cast times and time delayed damage application, this playstyle is very skill reliant and a lot less forgiving. It allows for a decent amount of skill expressions by knowing what to do in any given situation as well as being aware of boss patterns and when it phases.

Stat Allocation

Option 1: spec/crit, highest ceiling spec build

Option 2: spec/swift, comfier spec build
Option 3: swift/crit, somewhat similar to casting flux, comparable damage to spec/swift

Engravings

Here are the Engravings you should aim to use,

and why you would choose specific combinations of Engravings to make a build.

Mandatory

Master Summoner

Reduced Wisdom Orbs cost for Spirit Summoning Skills by 1. Damage of Normal Skills and Spirit Summoning Skills +2/5/10% and Crit Rate +3/8/16%

  • This is mandatory to run on Spec Summoner. It gives you bonus damage and crit rate on all your normal and identity spells. It also reduces the cost of your identity by -1 orb and adds secondary effects on each Ancient Spirit increasing her overall effectiveness and versatility immensely.

Grudge

+4/10/20% Damage

+20% Received Damage

  • This is the best permanent damage engraving that every DPS classes should get.

Keen Blunt Weapon

+10/25/50% Crit Damage

10% Chance of

-20% Damage

  • Summoner has no built in Crit Damage in her kit so KBW is extremely important to take because of the value it brings.
  • Due to your self crit buff this engraving is incredibly efficient in all builds.
  • This efficiency increases with party synergies.

Raid Captain

+10/22/45% of Bonus Move Speed as Damage

+4/8.8/18% Damage

at max Move Speed (140%)

  • This is only for Swift Master Summoner. High Swiftness combined with Yearning will allow you to be very efficient with this engraving. Using this on Spec is a straight dps loss whichever variant you try.

Pick Two

Hit master

+3/8/16% Damage to

Non-Directional Attacks

  • Solid 16% Damage Increase since our skills are non-directional. However, it doesn't affect Awakening damage.

Cursed Doll

+3/8/16% Attack Power

-25% Healing

  • Is only 15% due to being additive with Adrenaline and has a negative penalty. Which can be felt on summoner since we are an immobile class.

All Out Attack

+4/10/20% Damage

+5/10/20% Cast Speed to

Holding & Casting Attacks

  • This is only for Swift Master Summoner.

Level 1

Adrenaline

+0.3/0.6/1% Attack Power

per Stack

+5/10/15% Crit Rate at

Max (6) Stacks

  • This is one of our best levels 1 engravings if we do not already run it at 3, this is due to how efficient the damage gain is.

Ether Predator

+0.2/0.3/0.5% Attack Power +0.3/0.6/1% Defense Per

Stack, Max 30 Stacks

  • For 5X3 +1, Ether Predator is a really good option for +1. It offers +6% extra Atk. Power and +9% armor at 30 stacks which has very high value for only a level 1 engraving.

Not Recommended

Mass Increase

+4/10/18% Attack Power

-10% Attack Speed

  • This makes the Summoner even slower than it already is. Just don’t

Precise Dagger

+4/10/20% Crit Rate

-12% Crit Damage

  • We don’t need this to have a decent crit rate, and we lose crit damage as well. Just not worth

Awakening

Bagron’s Wrath

Summon quicksand. After some time, Bagron jumps out of the sand,dealing damage to foes at the center of the quicksand and launching them into the air. Bagron then bites the foes in the air, dealing damage and slamming them down onto the ground.

This is used for the large amount of meter generation it provides for us.

Bagron’s Wrath is very important to maximize the biggest amount of burst spec build can do. Please refer to the opener rotation guide below for further explanation.

Rotations

Pre-summon

ALWAYS DO THIS FIRST before you do anything else. 

Summon these right before the boss spawns, not during mechanics because you’ll waste the adrenaline stack and you might have to reapply Shurdi during a burst window which is a dps loss.

Stagger

(or)

Opener/ Triple Akir combo

To effectively pull this off you must start off with a full identity gauge. Due to Bagron’s being multi-hit it can fill your identity gauge by 180% and preemptively casting Electric Storm first allows you effectively fill the last 20% of identity with the ticking during the opener. How you achieve maximum benefit from your awakening is by using Akir immediately after using Bagron’s to empty the gauge while the animation for Bagron’s persists.

You must animation cancel >  and  > .

Be quick with executing your spells during the combo.

Alternative Triple Akir combo

Note that these versions do less dmg because your last Akir, Spear and Earth Collapse are not inside your Attack-Power buff window.

Keep on Cooldown

Use storm off cooldown and cancel it if possible. Try to space Water Elemental and Steeds for Adrenaline upkeep.

  • You ALWAYS want to have attack power buffs for , but holding identity too long can cause a DPS damage loss. Which is why you must have sufficient CD reduction on  and  to match the rate you gain enough identity gauge to use .

  • Learn how to animation cancel  and  to maximize as much identity gauge generation you can in between .

  • You have to be able to predict boss movement and positioning by learning boss patterns to maximize  and meter generation skills.

  • If you cancel  with  (>>) at full meter, don’t cancel  with . You will overcap your meter and thus delay your next Akir because you won’t have skill up to fill the meter. Not using  will allow you to use it to generate the last remaining meter for your next Akir.

  • Try to full meter during mechanics/damage reduction phases so you can Akir right after the mechanics. The same can be done for stagger checks but use with caution. Greeding for it can make you wipe the raid.

FAQ: Master Summoner

Questions sourced from frequent interactions within the Unofficial Lost Ark Discord

Should I go Cursed Doll or Hit Master?

Either or is acceptable. Hit Master does not affect your awakening, so if that bothers you then Cursed Doll is the better option. Once you are able to achieve 60+% crit rate without Adrenaline 3 you can replace it with Cursed Doll and run Adrenaline +1 for a 5x3 +1 set up.

Can I replace Adrenaline?

Only if you are able to achieve a minimum 60% crit rate in a 5x3+1 set up.

Can I play this early game?

Seeing that you really only need to focus on one damage gem might be appealing as a cheap alt. However if you want to play this build effectively it really only shines with high Spec and high level CDR gems to have a proper rotation with consistent uptime. It is technically playable.

Is Swift MS a viable build?

Yes, it does comparable dmg to Spec/Swift MS if you have the uptime.

Is Salvation still a viable build?

If your necklace is Spec/Crit and you have a crit synergy/ lvl 3 Adrenaline engraving/  9/7 stone/ a good crit bracelet/ another crit synergy. If at least one of mentioned criteria has been met, you may opt for Salvation over Hallucination, BUT ONLY if your necklace is Crit/Spec.

Are level 7 gems ok?

Level 7 cooldown gems are good enough, however if you want to play Hallu Spec/Crit then having higher cooldown gems is recommended because of the lack of Cooldown Reduction.

Why Flash Explosion?

Flash Explosion has its niche use in primarily keeping up Adrenaline during phases and mechanics. At the loss of stagger and direct meter generation, you have a lower cooldown skill with similar meter/s generation(if you keep casting it off cooldown). It is less likely that you will be overcapping meter with Flash Explosion than with Steeds and thus make the subsequent Akir faster (if you try to cast it off cd as often as you can). You can put Flash Explosion to LVL 10 but apart from comfort it won’t really do much damage overall. Having Flash Explosion gem at LVL 7 is also enough to keep Adrenaline up, even as Spec/Crit Summoner.

Why Pauru?

Pauru is quite a versatile skill. Primarily you can use a Triple Akir opener with 6 stacks of Adrenaline with Pauru and it is easier to keep up Adrenaline compared to Steeds. As well as having 2 variations of the opener.

It also allows you to send Ancient Spear and Earth Collapse outside of your standard AP windows to fill up your meter in case you lack meter to use Akir and not waste the dmg those skills provide.  And you can use it to greed dmg before or in between non-dr phases. If you are using Fiery Boom it is recommended to use Blue Wealth on it and not to detonate it for the Attack Power buff directly after summoning it. Pauru builds as much meter as Steeds does but over a longer duration, so to optimize this skill you want to have Pauru up for a while before detonating it. Not Detonating Pauru also still allows you to get the Attack Power buff but it can overlap with your other Attack Power buffs and since it does not stack thus wasting it. Detonating Pauru counts as multiple normal auto attacks in meter generation so you could detonate Pauru in case you miss a tiny bit meter to get another Akir of.

Communication Overflow

Written by Mugician, Zaee, Ilyora, and Ippotsuko

Playstyle

Communication Overflow is a swiftness based Pet build which utilizes Pets to deal most of its DPS. Due to high swiftness it is a relatively safer variant with incredibly consistent DPS since the pets cannot be killed *except Maririn, but has a huge HP pool* and only die to time expiration. This class engraving has one of the most active playstyles in the game, looking at 45 spell casts per min being your low end with 55+ being average. If you love microing pets, like managing buff uptime, being fast and adaptable, and enjoy always pressing buttons this is a great class for you.

Stagger

(or if +1 ms) or

Your rotation changes depending on what your 2 non-pet damage skills are (Ancient Spear and Steed Charge/Earth Collapse/Winged Spirit).

The general idea is to try and sync each of your 2 non-pet damage skills with either your Moss/Water combo or Elcid. Whichever you pick depends on your preference and your tripods/gems.

For starters it is recommended to try and sync Ancient Spear with Lily and Earth Collapse with your Moss/Water combo. It is a bit scuffed without any tripod levels but there is no better option. .

Eventually, once you have the proper tripods for it, you can try to sync Ancient Spear with your Moss/Water combo and Earth collapse with Elcid. This allows you to cast Ancient Spear off cooldown which is more DPS in theory.

However, beware that this is much harder to pull off in practice. Since Ancient Spear and Moss have almost the exact same cooldown, your rotation is highly susceptible to desync if you can't cast Spear immediately after your Moss/Water combo.

If you are using Ali always cancel spear with it, if you are using Akir use it before your moss/water ele>spear combo, if your Earth Collapse  is up you can optionally cancel spear with Earth Collapse to squeeze some extra damage out.

FAQ: Communication Overflow

Questions sourced from frequent interactions within the Unofficial Lost Ark Discord

Is Summoner a good alt if she is expensive?

Summoner is not an overly expensive alt anymore with express events mostly hitting most gear points you would need.

Is Communication Overflow easy?

Difficulty is very subjective in this game so it’s hard to really say what makes a class difficult, as some people may find emperor arcana difficult while others find it very easy. Generally CO is not an easy class being a high apm with easy to miss abilities having to manage many things at a time. Overall MS and CO are about similar difficulty and you could swing either way on which is harder for you based on many factors.

Can I run the Nightmare set ?

No, Nightmare is awful for Communication Overflow (and summoner in general). Reason being is that a lot of her DPS output does not use mana (awakening, pet actives, and identity) therefore not getting the damage bonus from Nightmare. This makes Nightmare an awful choice for Summoner

Can I replace Adrenaline?

No, you are heavily reliant on critting and it is a DPS loss, this is mainly because of the KBW efficiency.

Do I need double class engraving?

Early on you do not need to run double class engraving, especially if you are not a huge spender/lucky to force a 9/7 rock to build 5x3 +1 pre-ancient. However once you are 1540 it allows us to build +1 engraving very easily. Our best +1 engraving is Master Summoner because of the value it offers making every other engraving weaker in comparison currently.

Conviction and Judgment? What’s that?

Conviction - Chance to proc on hit with the skill it is attached to and gain a ‘Conviction’ Buff.

Judgment - Chance to proc on hit with the skill it is attached to and gain a ‘Judgment’ Buff. Consumes Conviction. When consumed, gain Combat Resource Recovery by 100% and reduce skill cooldowns by 15% (multiplicative) for 6 seconds. 30 sec cooldown on buff ending until ‘Conviction’ can proc again.

We use this to make sure we don’t run out of mana. It also helps a bit with cooldowns.

Any gem or tripod requirements?

Level 7 gems are just enough to be viable.
For tripods, get high value ones to 5 as soon as possible (with lvl 5 wish amulets it shouldn’t be too hard), the rest are viable at 4 and slowly get them up as you play.

What happened to Charming and Salvation builds?

These two builds have mostly become redundant with express events launching you past any point you’d be using either build.
